$ System.MarshalByRefObject (class)

`System.MarshalByRefObject` derives from → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Object[`System.Object`]

`System.MarshalByRefObject` is the base class for object that need to marshal their data accross application boundaries.

Objects that don't inherit from `System.MarshalByRefObject` are able to marshal their data *by value*.

A prominent class that derives from `MarshalByRefObject` is → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/__ComObject[`System.__ComObject`].
